# ── Canonical reference screens: PRIVATE BY DEFAULT (RULE: keep private screens out of GitHub) ──
# The whole canonical-screens folder stays ignored. Structural ground truth ships as .md + the .fig.
# Raw PNGs are private unless EXPLICITLY allowlisted below. A NEW screenshot is private automatically —
# never public by forgetting a blacklist line (that is how leaks happened twice). To publish one,
# add an explicit `!docs/canonical-screens/<file>.png` line here AND confirm with the user first.
docs/canonical-screens/*.png
docs/canonical-screens/_private-refs/
# Explicit public allowlist — user-confirmed public (2026-07-16, "Privacy: 6"):
!docs/canonical-screens/01-design-system-governance-console.png
